The '''chief research officer''' ('''CRO'''), '''research officer''', or '''research director''', is a job title commonly given to the most senior executive in an enterprise responsible for the [[research]] that supports enterprise goals. Generally, the CRO reports to the [[chief executive officer]], [[chief operating officer]], or [[chief financial officer]]. In educational organizations, they report to the [[Chancellor (education)|Chancellor or President]].<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Dean O. | first1 = Smith | title = Managing the Research University |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=neZkJ6kKhlUC | publisher = Oxford University Press | year = 2011 | accessdate = 2013-08-23 | isbn = 978-0199793259}}</ref>

